lear matter becomes more\ntransparent at the highest RHIC energy compared to lower RHIC energies. The\ncontribution of heavier hadronic resonance decay is taken into account.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Dec 2014 13:20:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-12-09"}
